ou want to be? If not, readjust your focus. It''s your future. Go get it!', 9209, 0), (388193, 'It is not that we have too little time to do all the things we need to do , it is that we feel the need to do too many things in the time we have.', 6402, 0), (388194, 'Our lives are made up of time, and the quality of our existence depends on our wise use of the moments we are given.', 30188, 0), (388195, 'Task switching exacts a cost few realize they are even paying.', 6402, 0), (388196, 'It''s not a good idea to cut back indiscriminately on what you read. The reason is that reading can save you time, because it gives you the opportunity to learn from other people''s experience.', 32385, 0), (388197, 'Time is a most versatile resource. It flies, marches on, works wonders, and will tell. It also runs out.', 32385, 0), (388198, 'There is no such thing as time management. There is only the mindset that optimally manages the self and its actions.', 19542, 0), (388199, 'He put this engine [a silver pocket watch] into our ears, which made an incessant noise, like that of a water-mill: and we conjecture it is either some unknown animal, or the god that he worships; but we are more inclined to the latter opinion, because he assured us, (if we understood him right, for he expressed himself very imperfectly) that he seldom did any thing without consulting it. He called it his oracle, and said, it pointed out the time for every action of his life.', 995, 0), (388200, 'Time is not waiting for you ', 61351, 0);
